result.name: Sky Cuisine (Sheung Wan)

reviews.text:
2 of us had lunch here!

Cheung Fun skin was too thick, and beef volume was rather low and tasteless.

Turnip cakes too soft, very big in size, but pointless given the taste was average.

Beef stomach was well made, soften and braised to a chewy yet sauce soaked finish.

Steamed lotus seed buns were fresh and good.

Overall not value for money, reasonable service, and probably will consider other options next time.
good food, good service and competitive price, worth to dine in

looks a great place well placed but service was pretty bad. most dishes ordered ended up with the staff offering alternative suggestion but that too ends up with another person coming up telling us they don't have that dish anymore as well. food itself was mediocre. at the end they offered the traditional Chinese dessert soup then comes and tell us they don't have it. final straw was when we had to ask for the bill 3 times and wait 15 minutes before it finally came. there was only 2 or 3 other customers at the time.
nice place and delicious dim sum for yum cha. also good service rendered by the staff.

Multi storey restaurant with only one very small lift. Better to save time and take the stairs if you can. Overall, decent food. But quite shocked that some of the beef in the beef fried ho fan were half raw. But then the kitchen must be very busy as it was the chinese new year.

result.name: 星月樓 上環店

reviews.text: 台於台太接近,坐位坐之間太窄,洗手間流水,衛生麻麻,食品好多ㄧ籠點心德3件,價💰不是平價
中上環之間，交通方便，地铁在旁，食物幾好，欵式亦多，價錢適中，只不過服務員態度麻麻，没有笑容，但結帳時有很多次將人數加多，若不察覺便多收了茶錢，不知是否有人作怪而公司不察覺，所以每次我都特別留神。
一早要搵位，過咗12點半一枱難求。
